citeinfo.title: Slaty-backed Gulls of the Teuri Island, Hokkaido, Japan

descript.abstract:
Data parameters include number of nests, time of egg laying, time of hatching, egg size, clutch size, hatching success, number of fledgling per nest, chick growth rate, and prey composition.
[ Reference: PICES Scientific Report No. 18 2001, Proceedings of the PICES/CoML/IPRC Workshop on "Impact of Climate Variability on Observation and Prediction of Ecosystem and Biodiversity Changes in the North Pacific", http://www.pices.int/publications/scientific_reports/Report18/default.aspx. ]
descript.purpose: To analyze how annual variation of physical marine processes in the northern part of the Japan Sea affect seabird breeding performance through fish stock change.
